disown [ job ... ]
job ... &|
job ... &!
       Remove the specified jobs from the job table; the shell will no longer report their status, and will not complain  if 
       interactive shell with them running or stopped.  If no job is specified, disown the current job.

       If the jobs are currently stopped and the AUTO CONTINUE option is not set, a warning is printed containing information
       running after they have been disowned.  If one of the latter two forms is used, the jobs will automatically be made ru
       the setting of the AUTO CONTINUE option.
